edu.rit.util

Class BitSet64

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.rit.util.BitSet64
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Streamable

    public class BitSet64
extends Object
implements Streamable
    Class BitSet64 provides a set of integers from 0 to 63. The set elements are stored in a bitmap representation.

    The bitmap representation is a value of type long. Bit 0 of the bitmap (the least significant bit) corresponds to set element 0, bit 1 of the bitmap (the next least significant bit) corresponds to set element 1, and so on. A bit of the bitmap is 1 if the set contains the corresponding element; a bit of the bitmap is 0 if the set does not contain the corresponding element.

    Note: Class BitSet64 is not multiple thread safe.
